  structures like boxes or walls."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.301097Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28836-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Mass, shape, volume and depth are used to draw the viewer’s attention to certain
  areas, enhancing the composition."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.301101Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28836-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Depth can help to establish the relationship between different elements, making the
  composition more dynamic."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.301105Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28836-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Variations in volume and depth can create visual intrigue, making a piece more
  engaging to look at."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.301109Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28673-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Portraits can show a person’s identity, including culture, gender, age, social
  status and background"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.304026Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28673-2
